</div>
</div>

<article class="ml-4 mt-8">
<h2>Interests</h2>
<ul>
<li>Quantum information: Foundation of quantum mechanics by information processing, nonlocality, generalized probabilistic theories, quantum computation.</li>
<li>Information theory: Low-density parity-check codes, belief propagation, graph covers, polar codes.</li>
<li>Computer science: Constraint satisfaction problems, fully polynomial-time approximation scheme for &#35;P-complete problems, holographic transformation, quantum computation.</li>
<li>Statistical physics: The Bethe approximation, cluster expansions, partition function zeros, replica method.</li>
</ul>
</article>
<article class="ml-4 mt-8">
<article>
<h2>Biography</h2>
<ul>
<li>Apr. 2023&ndash; ,  Current position.</li>
<li>Jan. 2015&ndash; Mar. 2023,  Assistant Professor at Tokyo Institute of Technology.</li>
<li>Apr. 2013&ndash; Dec. 2014,  Postdoctoral Fellow at Tokyo Institute of Technology.</li>
<li>Apr. 2010&ndash; Mar. 2013,  Ph.D. in Informatics, Kyoto University, Kyoto, Japan.</li>
<li>Apr. 2008&ndash; Mar. 2010,  Master of Informatics at Graduate School of Informatics, Kyoto University, Kyoto, Japan.</li>
<li>Apr. 2000&ndash; Mar. 2008,  Bachelor  of Engineering at Tokyo Institute of Technology, Tokyo, Japan.</li>
</ul>
</article>
</Layout>
